Interface ListInterface<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - 
    public interface ListInterface<T>
    A ListInterface is a container that supports insertion, removal, and searching.
    Author:
    jcollard, jddevaug

      • insertAt

        ListInterface<T> insertAt​(int index,
                          T elem)
        Adds an element at the specified index such that a subsequent call to get(int) at index will return the inserted value. This method runs in O(index) time. For convenience, this method returns the ListInterface that was modified.
        Parameters:
        index - the index to add the element at
        elem - the element to add
        Returns:
        The modified ListInterface
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if elem is null
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index is less than 0 or greater than size()

        Removes the first element from this ListInterface and returns it. This method runs in O(1) time.
        Returns:
        the removed element
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the ListInterface is empty.

      • remove

        boolean remove​(T elem)
        Removes elem from this ListInterface if it exists. If multiple instances of elem exist in this ListInterface the one associated with the smallest index is removed. This method runs in O(size) time.
        Parameters:
        elem - the element to remove
        Returns:
        true if this ListInterface was altered and false otherwise.

      • contains

        int contains​(T elem)
        Returns the smallest index which contains elem. If there is no instance of elem in this ListInterface then -1 is returned. This method runs in O(size) time.
        Parameters:
        elem - the element to search for
        Returns:
        the smallest index which contains elem or -1 if elem is not in this ListInterface

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if this ListInterface contains no elements and false otherwise. This method runs in O(1) time.
        Returns:
        true if this ListInterface contains no elements and false otherwise.
